headlines.description: — Franz Wagner had 20 points, nine rebounds, eight assists and two blocks, and the Orlando Magic claimed their sixth straight win, and second in three days over the Nets, with a 100-92 victory against Brooklyn on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic beat Nets 100-92 for 2nd win over Brooklyn in 3 days

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. had 25 points, eight rebounds and three blocks as the Memphis Grizzlies erased a 19-point first-half deficit and defeated the Indiana Pacers 136-121 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson's 25 points rally Grizzlies from 19-point deficit to 136-121 win over Pacers

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 20 of his 35 points in the fourth quarter as the Cleveland Cavaliers ended Boston's seven-game winning streak with a 115-111 victory over the Celtics on Sunday night in the second intense matchup between the Eastern...
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 35, Cavs end Celtics' winning streak with 115-111 win in matchup of East's elite

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Mikal Bridges scored 31 points, Karl-Anthony Towns had 14 points and 19 rebounds, and the New York Knicks beat the injury-depleted New Orleans Pelicans 118-85 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mikal Bridges scores 31, Knicks beat injury-depleted Pelicans 118-85

headlines.description: — RJ Barrett scored 37 points, Scottie Barnes had 23 points and 10 rebounds, and the Toronto Raptors beat the Miami Heat 119-116 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barrett scores 37, Barnes adds 23 points and 10 rebounds as Raptors beat Heat 119-116

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet had a season-high 38 points and Dillon Brooks made a go-ahead jump shot late to help the Houston Rockets to a 119-116 win over the Oklahoma City Thunder Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: VanVleet has season-high 38 to lead Rockets to 119-116 win over Thunder

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis had 33 points and 11 rebounds, LeBron James added 27 points and 14 assists, and the short-handed Los Angeles Lakers beat the Utah Jazz 105-104 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Davis scores 33, LeBron James takes over late as Lakers hold on to beat Jazz 105-104

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic returned from a wrist injury and had 36 points in the Dallas Mavericks' 137-131 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic has 36 points and 13 assists in return, Mavericks down the Trail Blazers 137-131

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama had 34 points, 13 rebounds and 11 assists for his first triple-double of the season, and the San Antonio Spurs beat the Sacramento Kings 127-125 on Sunday for their fifth win in six games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Victor Wembanyama has first triple double of season to lead Spurs past Kings 127-125

headlines.description: — James Harden scored 39 points — making all 13 of his free throws — and the Los Angeles Clippers overcame Nikola Jokic’s triple-double to beat the Denver Nuggets 126-122 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden scores 37 and Clippers overcome Jokic's triple-double to beat Nuggets 126-122
